<emphasis id="B929EAFB47744D119BE2FC72FE85FBEB" bold="true" box="[160,276,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="128">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE236E947744D129BE2FB8EFE0AFDA5" blockId="9.[160,1156,1007,1137]" lastBlockId="10.[160,1155,142,583]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="129" pageId="9" pageNumber="128">
Within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A47744D119A67FB8EFE10FBCE" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[293,385,1043,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB47744D119A67FB8EFE10FBCE" box="[293,385,1043,1068]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="128">globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, only 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A47744D11995EFB8EFD13FBCE" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes" authorityYear="2016" box="[540,642,1043,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benesi">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB47744D11995EFB8EFD13FBCE" box="[540,642,1043,1068]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="128">D. benesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A47744D119986FB8EFC39FBCE" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[708,936,1043,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellatopunctatus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB47744D119986FB8EFC39FBCE" box="[708,936,1043,1068]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="128">D. ocellatopunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are brachypterous species. They are associated with mountain formations; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC4B1847744D11985DFBA8FB15FBAC" author="Vaz-de-Mello FZ &amp; Nunes RV" box="[799,1156,1077,1102]" pageId="9" pageNumber="128" pagination="294 - 300" refId="ref15886" refString="Vaz-de-Mello FZ, Nunes RV. 2016. New species, redescription and taxonomic notes in the Dichotomius (Selenocopris) batesi (Harold) species-group (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Zootaxa. 4139 (2): 294 - 300." type="journal article" year="2016">Vaz-de-Mello and Nunes (2016)</bibRefCitation>
provided detailed descriptions for both species, and illustrated the tegmen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A47744D119F58FBC5FBECFB93" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes" authorityYear="2016" box="[1050,1149,1112,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benesi">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB47744D119F58FBC5FBECFB93" box="[1050,1149,1112,1137]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="128">D. benesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, herein the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A47774D129973FF13FD02FF45" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes" authorityYear="2016" box="[561,659,142,167]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benesi">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB47774D129973FF13FD02FF45" box="[561,659,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">D. benesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is merely complemented by the inclusion of the following characters of the male genitalia: in dorsal view, paramera rectangular, onethird longer than its width at medial portion; apex slightly obliqualy truncate; surface with a feeble pre-apical longitudinal carina, inner edge curved inward at basal third (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C47774D129F65FF6BFB12FEED" box="[1063,1155,246,271]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1113,1136]" captionTargetBox="[172,1143,152,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-135@7.[163,1153,142,1082]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Tegmen, dorsal and ventral views,respectively. (a,b) Dichotomius benesi; (c,d) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (e,f) D. femoratus; (g,h) D. fortepunctatus; (i,j) D. gamboaensis. Scale bar: 500 µm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530260" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530260/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(a)); in lateral view, apical half of paramera approximately as wide as base; ventral sclerotised membrane between paramera thinner at basal half, slightly angulate laterally (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C47774D129BEAFEC3FE9AFE95" box="[168,267,350,375]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1113,1136]" captionTargetBox="[172,1143,152,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-135@7.[163,1153,142,1082]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Tegmen, dorsal and ventral views,respectively. (a,b) Dichotomius benesi; (c,d) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (e,f) D. femoratus; (g,h) D. fortepunctatus; (i,j) D. gamboaensis. Scale bar: 500 µm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530260" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530260/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(b)). ME with two hook-like projections inferiorly, projections separated by a broad U-shaped emargination; ME with a longitudinal fold at the median inferior region (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C47774D129BEAFE39FE99FE5F" box="[168,264,420,445]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1177,1200]" captionTargetBox="[164,1149,143,1139]" captionTargetId="figure-128@8.[163,1153,142,1145]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Endophallites. (a) Dichotomius benesi, endophallus with endophallites, dorsal view. Medial endophallite: (b) D. benesi; (c) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (d,e) D. femoratus; (f) D. fortepunctatus; (g) D. gamboaensis. Accessory endophallites: (h) D. benesi; (i) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (j) D. femoratus; (k) D. fortepunctatus; (l) D. gamboaensis. Abbreviations: FLP, fronto-lateral peripherical endophallite; A +SA, subaxial and axial endophallites; SRP, superior-right peripheral endophallite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530262/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(b)). Complex of A and A+SA endophallites thin, C-shaped in lateral view; SA endophallite with reticulate texture inferiorly (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C47774D12998CFE5BFCA2FE3D" box="[718,819,454,479]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1177,1200]" captionTargetBox="[164,1149,143,1139]" captionTargetId="figure-128@8.[163,1153,142,1145]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Endophallites. (a) Dichotomius benesi, endophallus with endophallites, dorsal view. Medial endophallite: (b) D. benesi; (c) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (d,e) D. femoratus; (f) D. fortepunctatus; (g) D. gamboaensis. Accessory endophallites: (h) D. benesi; (i) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (j) D. femoratus; (k) D. fortepunctatus; (l) D. gamboaensis. Abbreviations: FLP, fronto-lateral peripherical endophallite; A +SA, subaxial and axial endophallites; SRP, superior-right peripheral endophallite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530262/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(h), arrow). FLP endophallite C-shaped in lateral right view, inferior region thinner than superior one; surface of the C-shaped region with irregular projections (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C47774D1299CFFD91FD7BFDC7" box="[653,746,524,549]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1177,1200]" captionTargetBox="[164,1149,143,1139]" captionTargetId="figure-128@8.[163,1153,142,1145]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Endophallites. (a) Dichotomius benesi, endophallus with endophallites, dorsal view. Medial endophallite: (b) D. benesi; (c) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (d,e) D. femoratus; (f) D. fortepunctatus; (g) D. gamboaensis. Accessory endophallites: (h) D. benesi; (i) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (j) D. femoratus; (k) D. fortepunctatus; (l) D. gamboaensis. Abbreviations: FLP, fronto-lateral peripherical endophallite; A +SA, subaxial and axial endophallites; SRP, superior-right peripheral endophallite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530262/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(h)). SRP endophallite approximately J-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C47774D129A51FDB3FEE1FDA5" box="[275,368,558,583]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1177,1200]" captionTargetBox="[164,1149,143,1139]" captionTargetId="figure-128@8.[163,1153,142,1145]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Endophallites. (a) Dichotomius benesi, endophallus with endophallites, dorsal view. Medial endophallite: (b) D. benesi; (c) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (d,e) D. femoratus; (f) D. fortepunctatus; (g) D. gamboaensis. Accessory endophallites: (h) D. benesi; (i) D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (j) D. femoratus; (k) D. fortepunctatus; (l) D. gamboaensis. Abbreviations: FLP, fronto-lateral peripherical endophallite; A +SA, subaxial and axial endophallites; SRP, superior-right peripheral endophallite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530262/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(h)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
